value.title: Los Angeles Times mocked after dedicating new beat to celebrating Kamala Harris: ‘Blatant hagiography’
value.excerpt: The Los Angeles Times was ridiculed on social media Tuesday after announcing it would launch "Covering Kamala Harris," a project described as "a beat dedicated to her historic rise to the White House.

value.title: Psaki walks back Biden comments on COVID-19 vaccine availability, says won't be widely available by spring
value.excerpt: White House Press Secretary Jen Psaki walked back President Biden’s comments that the majority of Americans would be vaccinated by the spring, telling reporters on Tuesday that the vaccine will not be widely available by then.

value.title: 'Same problems' will resurface if Biden rolls back border wall construction, former NM governor warns
value.excerpt: Former New Mexico Republican Gov. Susana Martinez warned Tuesday that it is 'very wrong' for the Biden administration to halt the construction of the southern border wall, calling the fence a 'piece of the security of our nation.'

value.title: RNC Chair Ronna McDaniel says Trump’s ‘not going to start a third party’
value.excerpt: Republican National Committee (RNC) chair Ronna McDaniel says she’s confident that former President Trump won’t start a splinter party.

value.title: Schumer suggests Biden declare 'climate emergency'
value.excerpt: Senate Democratic Leader Chuck Schumer suggested Monday that President Biden consider declaring an emergency on climate change.

value.title: Haley says Biden rejoining UN Human Rights Council would 'fly in the face' of rights push
value.excerpt: Former U.N. Ambassador Nikki Haley on Monday warned that a potential move by President Biden to rejoin the controversial U.N. Human Rights Council would "fly in the face" of the fight for human rights.

value.title: Biden's White House victory fueled by record-shattering $145M in 'dark money,' report says
value.excerpt: For years, Democrats have railed against anonymous campaign contributions as a uniquely corrupting political force — even as President Biden benefited from a record-shattering amount of "dark money" donations during the 2020 election.

value.title: Hannity says Biden’s policies will 'fail’ while media takes ‘sycophantic vacation’
value.excerpt: "Hannity" host Sean Hannity criticizes President Biden's beginnings in office and forecasts a disastrous end.

value.title: Trump endorses Sarah Huckabee Sanders for Arkansas governor
value.excerpt: Former President Donald Trump endorsed Sarah Huckabee Sanders in her run for Arkansas governor on Monday night.

value.title: Biden declines to tell Chicago teachers refusing to teach in-person to go back to work
value.excerpt: President Biden declined to tell Chicago teachers on Monday to return to school following a union vote over the weekend to defy a district order for educators to return to campuses in order to prepare to resume in-person classroom instruction.

value.title: Rep. Crenshaw on Biden lifting transgender military ban: 'People should serve openly'
value.excerpt: Any American willing and able to serve in the military should be permitted to do so, Rep. Dan Crenshaw, R-Texas, said Monday after President Biden lifted a Trump-era restriction on transgender people serving their country.

value.title: Democrats showing 'shockingly bad judgment' with Trump impeachment focus: Cornyn
value.excerpt: Sen. John Cornyn, R-Texas, admonished Democrats against pursuing another impeachment trial against former President Donald Trump, saying Monday it shows "shockingly bad judgment."

value.title: Fauci, Birx were right to stay on Trump coronavirus task force, former surgeon general says
value.excerpt: Former Surgeon General Dr. Jerome Adams defended Trump administration coronavirus task force members Dr. Anthony Fauci and Dr. Deborah Birx over criticism that they should have quit working for former President Donald Trump.

value.title: 1 in 5 Americans have confidence Biden can unite the country: poll
value.excerpt: Just one in five Americans have “a great deal of confidence” in President Biden’s ability to make good on his goal to unify the country, according to a new poll released Sunday.

value.title: ABC's Matthew Dowd Compares Trump, GOP With Hitler, Tojo, KKK, Apartheid
value.excerpt: ABC News contributor Matthew Dowd commented Sunday on ABC's "This Week" roundtable: MATTHEW DOWD: Well, to me, the impeachment -- we have to separate the parts of the impeachment vote. I mean, other countries have gone through this before,

value.title: Biden may pick up the tab for San Francisco homeless hotels
value.excerpt: San Francisco hotels used to house homeless people may be fully funded by the federal government this year, thanks to an executive order signed by President Joe Biden signed last Thursday.

value.title: Kamala Harris' Roe v. Wade post draws Tennessee governor’s response: ‘Abortion isn’t healthcare’
value.excerpt: Tennessee Gov. Bill Lee spoke out last week after Vice President Kamala Harris issued a statement to mark the 48th anniversary of the Supreme Court decision that legalized abortion nationwide.

value.title: Biden, UK's Boris Johnson discuss Paris accord, trade, coronavirus
value.excerpt: President Biden had his first phone call with British Prime Minister Boris Johnson on Saturday, where Johnson pressed the new president for a U.S.-U.K. trade deal.

value.title: Rep. Ilhan Omar calls on Biden to back 'recurring cash payments' until economy recovers
value.excerpt: Omar and other progressives have argued that Biden’s proposal does not go far enough to address the current financial crisis.

value.title: Trump impeachment trial delayed until week of Feb. 8, Schumer says
value.excerpt: Senate Majority Leader Chuck Schumer, D-N.Y., said on Friday lawmakers will wait to carry out President Donald Trump’s impeachment hearings for several weeks, following a brief standoff on Capitol Hill over timing.

value.title: Biden says 'nothing we can do' to change pandemic 'trajectory' in coming months
value.excerpt: Biden addressed his administration’s response efforts during a press briefing on two executive orders meant to provide food assistance to low-income families and protect workers’ rights during the pandemic.

value.title: Ari Fleischer: 'Big government is back' under Biden
value.excerpt: President Biden's approach to tackling the economic crisis brought about by the coronavirus pandemic shows that "big government is back" in Washington, former White House Press Secretary Ari Fleischer said Friday.

value.title: Reince Priebus: 'Tough time for the Republican Party’ but Biden's actions easy to unite against
value.excerpt: Former White House Chief of Staff Reince Priebus told "America’s Newsroom" Friday that it’s a "tough time for the Republican Party" since President Biden was sworn in, but Biden's actions may make it easier for the party to unite.

value.title: Biden suggests delayed impeachment timeline may be 'better'
value.excerpt: Biden suggested having more time to get his Cabinet nominees confirmed may help jumpstart his policy agenda.

value.title: Joe Biden putting 'Saudi Arabia first' by halting Keystone XL pipeline: Sen. Daines
value.excerpt: Sen. Steve Daines, R-Mont., believes President Biden killing the Keystone XL pipeline shows he’s putting "Saudi Arabia first," not American workers.

value.title: Kamala Harris, Doug Emhoff will stay in Blair House while VP residence undergoes repairs
value.excerpt: This is the house where history will be made. Vice President Kamala Harris will soon be residing on the grounds of the Naval Observatory in northwestern Washington, D.C., in a home occupied by several of her predecessors.

value.title: Gingrich: Dems 'methodically trying to destroy conservatism' with Biden as 'pleasant cover'
value.excerpt: President Biden's "radical" inner circle is working to "destroy" the legacy of President Trump, former House Speaker Newt Gingrich warned on "Hannity" Thursday.

value.title: Biden proposes extending nuclear arms treaty with Russia for 5 years
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden has proposed extending a nuclear arms treaty with Russia before it expires next month, White House press secretary Jen Psaki said during a Thursday press conference.

value.title: Facebook Refers Trump Account Suspension to Oversight Board
value.excerpt: The social-media company said a decision from its independent panel on the matter—the biggest issue it has tackled since being set up last year—would be binding.

value.title: Obama praises Biden's executive order blitz: 'This is a time for boldness'
value.excerpt: Former President Barack Obama praised President Biden on Thursday for enacting a sweeping slate of executive orders within hours of his inauguration as president.
